     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To his knowne Friend M<seg rend="sup">r</seg>. R BROME
on his Northern Lasse.</head>
   <l>MY Loue may wrong th<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>e, Friend; and, should I praise</l>
   <l>Thy <hi>Booke,</hi> I <gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap> 'twould stayne the wreathing Bayes</l>
   <l>That crownes thy Head: No, they that know, can tell</l>
   <l>This <hi>Piece</hi> craues not a bribing Prayer to sell.</l>
   <l>Here's <hi>Beauty, Wit,</hi> and <hi>Language</hi> in a Glasse.</l>
   <l>Who would not haue a Copy of this <hi>Lasse?</hi>
   </l>
</div>
